  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a criminal offense in most countries. It is typically covered under criminal legislation and financial crime laws. Money laundering involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Many nations have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations with criminal penalties, including fines and imprisonment, for those found guilty of such activities.",
